<subSubSection id="A068D6F17BCD68556FCB43DF63D56B88" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph id="95A7801BE16257F6869C1EEF630A0CF0" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39DB53ACC1DE16CFB278342C29681511" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="11404DDE8A6C02B139886F71F5E2DD1E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male</emphasis>
, wingspan 32 mm (Figs 
<figureCitation id="631C041CBA8F655CE7C149E98BE2EE19" captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Adults of Sacada spp. 7 S. unilinealis Hampson (male), India 8 S. unilinealis Hampson (male), holotype, Sikkim, India 9 S. inordinata (Walker) (male), holotype, Darjeeling, India 10 S. dzonguensis, sp. nov. (male), India. 11 S. umtasorensis, sp. nov. (male), India 12 S. pallescens Hampson (male), India. Scale bars: 5 mm (7, 10, 11); 12.7 mm (12)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443710" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="59F6D419849263C2C6F84A7A76C97888" captionStart="Figures 13–18" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 13 - 18. Adults of Sacada and Pseudosacada spp. 13 S. pallescens Hampson (male), lectotype, Bhutan 14 S. decora Walker, Singapore 15 Pseudosacada flexuosa (Snellen) (= Sybrida inflammealis Ragonot), India 16 P. flexuosa (Snellen) (male), Kanhmun, Mizoram, India 17 P. flexuosa (Snellen) (male), Umtasor, Meghalaya, India 18 P. flexuosa (Snellen) (male), Ganeshgudi, Karnataka, India. Scale bars: 5 mm (16 - 18)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures13-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443711" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">13</figureCitation>
). Pale rufous. Forewing speckled fuscous; a dark brownish basal spot; antemedial line smoothly curved; a speck on discocellular; postmedial line slightly curved below costa, then oblique to inner margin, some fuscous suffusion beyond it; cilia dark at tips; underside ochreous with rufous suffusion on basal half of costa, curved postmedial line present. Hindwing pale with indistinct, evenly curved postmedial line, crossed by a rufous streak on vein Cu2. Underside with curved postmedial line. 
<emphasis id="9DD5E048A77250BD62AB154B05D65B6A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="42222E908010CE9AB21E7C5E4E9A7B41" captionStart="Figures 27–32" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 27 - 32. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 27, 28 Male genitalia of S. dzonguensis, sp. nov. 29, 30 male genitalia of S. umtasorensis, sp. nov. 31, 32 male genitalia of S. pallescens Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures27-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443713" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F26E715ADBA8D6E6D625F0697F2AAEC2" captionStart="Figures 27–32" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 27 - 32. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 27, 28 Male genitalia of S. dzonguensis, sp. nov. 29, 30 male genitalia of S. umtasorensis, sp. nov. 31, 32 male genitalia of S. pallescens Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures27-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443713" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">32</figureCitation>
). Uncus broad with a fold on lateral side; gnathos well developed, tip hooked; valva simple, without any process; tegumen broad; transtilla broad, forming inverted omega (ω) shape; juxta short and broad, slightly constricted at apex; saccus long; vinculum U-shaped; aedeagus long, vesica membranous with fine scobination, cornuti absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91B836F072C32E80429F6810FEA156D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="564B13AE48745D399E8F0DFE155EEAD6" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29B49A229EE0F4CF24EDFE4B3D57B903" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName id="C413E98CE11A94A5FA89D61EE1855F4E" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Sacada" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sacada pallescens" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallescens">
<emphasis id="8F561A8F909C9187DC55EAEC2D0D8F5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Sacada pallescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unmistakable among the species studied due to the smoothly curved antemedial line (highly angled in other Indian species, except in 
<taxonomicName id="F64BC3711FF4B30EB5B8943A8E1FB00A" genus="S." lsidName="S. unilinealis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="unilinealis">
<emphasis id="EBF071A890CBF10927ED60BE66195081" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">S. unilinealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where it is absent) and hindwing which has a prominent rufous streak on vein Cu2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
